{"id":42744,"title":"Screening strategies for colorectal cancer in asymptomatic adults.","abstract":"This article provides an update for the primary care community on the evidence and recommendations for colorectal cancer screening in the adult population without symptoms at average and increased risk, excluding patients with high-risk genetic syndromes. The current and possible new screening strategies are reviewed, along with clinical wisdom related to the implementation of each method. ","date":"2014-05-16","categories":"Digestive System Diseases","split":"test","url":"http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/24830611","annotations":[{"name":"Colorectal cancer","weight":0.865242,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Colorectal_cancer"},{"name":"Genetics","weight":0.786341,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Genetics"},{"name":"Primary care","weight":0.765521,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Primary_care"},{"name":"Syndrome","weight":0.713417,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Syndrome"},{"name":"Cancer","weight":0.701318,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cancer"},{"name":"Symptom","weight":0.683991,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Symptom"},{"name":"Asymptomatic","weight":0.574262,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Asymptomatic"},{"name":"Screening (medicine)","weight":0.55166,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Screening_(medicine)"},{"name":"Adult","weight":0.525722,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Adult"},{"name":"Colon (anatomy)","weight":0.22573,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Colon_(anatomy)"},{"name":"Risk","weight":0.182524,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Risk"},{"name":"Cancer screening","weight":0.148784,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cancer_screening"},{"name":"Evidence-based medicine","weight":0.104746,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Evidence-based_me